Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff with cream slip. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Antimachos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0381.42.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0789)
